leadership_approach|vision_results_process_people|graduated|This leadership pattern moves in a clear order: Vision, Results, Process, then People. It works best when each later signal arrives before the first routes close the response too tightly.|The sequence gives leadership a practical rhythm. It helps people see what comes first, what needs support next, and where the response needs to widen.|The trap is stopping the sequence after Vision and Results. Process and People need space before the work becomes fixed around the first route.|Follow the order, but keep widening it as the work takes shape. Bring in structure and trust before the response feels finished.|Follow the sequence, then widen before the work closes in.|active|leadership_approach::vision_results_process_people::graduated
leadership_approach|vision_results_process_people|balanced|This leadership pattern gives several usable routes into the work. Its strength comes from naming the current leadership need before shifting emphasis.|Balanced leadership gives range across direction, outcomes, structure, and trust. It adapts well when the situation is named clearly.|The trap is moving between routes without naming the priority. Others lose confidence when they cannot tell which leadership need matters now.|Name the current need before changing emphasis. Then use the signal that fits the situation rather than trying to use every route at once.|Name the need, then lead from the signal that fits.|active|leadership_approach::vision_results_process_people::balanced
